-- MOVES-Brown Shipley names Roger Clark as head of wealth management
-- 
-- Tue Sep 30, 2014 04:51AM EDT
-- None



Sept 30 (Reuters) - UK-based private bank Brown Shipley appointed Roger Clark as head of wealth management.

He will be responsible for the ongoing management and development of wealth planning and pensions activities. Clark, who previously served as head of wealth solutions at private bank C Hoare & Co., will report to head of private banking Hugh Titcomb.